The Red Army invasion of Azerbaijan, also known as the Sovietization of
Azerbaijan, was a military campaign carried out by the 11th Army of Soviet
Russia on April 27 - May 1, 1920 to overthrow the government of Azerbaijan
Democratic Republic and to install a Bolshevik regime in the country.

